<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on Dates for Product, Service Price Changes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Dates for Product, Service Price Changes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2405185294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2405185294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As a reminder, next we reiterate the dates on which 
the new prices and fees on selected products and services 
established by accord of the Council of Ministers' executive 
committee will go into effect. 
  New prices for controlled-distribution cigarettes, rolled 
tobacco, beer, rum, brandy, and fuel for private vehicles will 
go into effect after the next sale cycle, which begins on 1 June. 
  New fees for electric service for homes will become 
effective 
on the basis of September consumption, which will be payable in 
October. 
  In the case of air and maritime transportation to and from 
the Isle of Youth, new prices will go into effect beginning 1 
June. Likewise, new prices for interprovincial bus and railroad 
transportation will go into efffect beginning 1 September, as 
will the new national and international postal and telegraph 
prices. 
  Water service fees for homes will increase on October 1, 
while retail food prices at workers' cafeterias will change 
beginning 1 July. 
  We also want to remind you that the accord of the Council of 
Ministers Executive Committee includes provisional increases in 
coastal transportation fees where required. These prices will be 
set definitely on 1 January 1995. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

