<F P=106> [From the "National Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] A Nicaraguan Foreign Affairs Ministry statement 
maintains that Nicaragua, as a UN member, is backing the 
measures adopted by the UN Security Council against Haiti's de 
facto military government, which is ruling that country. 
Nicaragua also backs the OAS measures and flatly rejects the 
human rights violations by the coupist military leadership. 

