  [Text] Sao Paulo, 24 May (AE) -- A luncheon hosted by Sao 
Paulo State Federation of Industries [FIESP] leaders for U.S. 
Treasury Assistant Secretary Lawrence Summers and Finance 
Minister Rubens Ricupero has just ended. The business people 
voiced satisfaction with the support shown by Summers for the 
Brazilian stabilization program. 
  Businessman Luiz Fernando Burlan of the Sadia Company said: 
"Summers came here as a U.S. Government representative and it is 
our impression that it is truly committed to Brazil. I for one 
was surprised by the way in which he conveyed the U.S. support 
for the plan." 
  Businessman Antonio Ermirio de Moraes said: "Summers has 
demonstrated that he has confidence in the plan." 
  Most of the business people who attended the luncheon ruled 
out the possibility of an outburst of consumption in the short 
term. 

