<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Antonio Marcello and Pamela Nunes] </F>
  [Excerpt] Brasilia, 24 May (AE) -- The next president of 
the Republic will be elected for a four-year term and will not 
be able to seek reelection. The Constituent Congress today 
approved for the second time a constitutional amendment that 
reduces the presidential term from five to four years. Of the 
357 congressmen in attendance, 323 voted in favor of the 
amendment, 29 voted against it, and five abstained. The 
possibility of an incumbent president seeking reelection already 
had been denied during the first vote taken on the issue. 
[passage omitted] 

