<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2505012894 </F>
<F P=103> PA2505012894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic developments monitored through 24 May 94. 
  According to a stock market report, net profits for the 
manufacturing sector rose 13.3 percent compared to the first 
quarter of 1993. The country's economic situation has not 
adversely affected Colombiana enterprises, which grew stronger 
in the first quarter, registering increases in sales and assets 
and decreasing indebtedness. The strengthening of the Colombian 
enterprises became evident in the growth of current assets and 
net worth, which rose 51.8 and 70.6 percent, respectively. 
(Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 20 May 94 pp 1B, 2B) 
  Colombian exports to Venezuela dropped 6.5 percent as a 
result of the bolivar devaluation. (Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras 
Caracol Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 24 May 94) 

</TEXT>

