<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today in Rome, Cuba's new ambassador to Italy Mario 
Rodriguez Martinez asserted that he is impressed by Italian 
President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro, to whom Rodriguez presented his 
credentials on 23 May. Rodriguez told journalists that Scalfaro 
turned out to be very much aware of the problems of Cuba and 
Latin America. 
  Rodriguez replaces Javier Ardizones, who was Cuba's 
ambassador to Italy for 10 years. Rodriguez added that among his 
goals are that of maintaining and further developing the already 
good political, economic, and trade relations with Italy and 
that of spreading the truth about Cuba. 
  Rodriguez was very much interested in getting to know the 
new 
Italian Government, which defines itself as centrist, and he 
reiterated that he is very pleased to have met with Scalfaro. 

