<F P=102>   FL2505182694 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2505182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Army General Staff has held a summit. 
High-ranking Armed Forces officers from units and garrisons of 
both Port-au- Prince and provincial towns gathered for a meeting 
at Army General Headquarters on 24 May. The meeting lasted 
several hours and focused on several current issues, said a 
source close to the military leadership. 
  Approximately 30 unit commanders gathered around the Army 
High Command to analyze the nation's overall situation. The 
measures taken after this meeting are unknown. Nevertheless, it 
should be recalled that the Haitian Army has been on maximum 
alert since 20 May, a few hours before the total embargo ordered 
by the United Nations against Haiti went into effect. 

</TEXT>

