<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dominican Republic Promises To Respect Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dominican Republic Promises To Respect Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2505190994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2505190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Dominican Republic has decided to respect the 
almost total embargo imposed on Haiti by the UN Security Council 
on 21 May. According to Fabio Herrera Cabral, the Dominican 
Government intends to deploy soldiers in the border areas to 
prevent leaks. Herrera added that Dominican Navy troops will be 
sent to prevent any and all Haitian initiatives to stock pile 
fuel via the sea. Haitian vessels that may try to reach the 
Dominican coasts to buy gasoline will not be authorized to pull 
into any Dominican port. 

</TEXT>

