He then went to EL ESPECTADOR, another important Colombian 
newspaper, where he spent approximately 20 minutes. 
  At 1120, he was received by Foreign Minister Sanin at the 
Foreign Ministry, from which they will travel to the 
Presidential Palace to meet President Gaviria. They will 
discuss bilateral integration and a ferry service that will 
begin operations in October or November. The ferry will link 
Panama to Colombia and the rest of South America. They will 
also discuss drug trafficking and the struggle the two countries 
are waging against it. 

</TEXT>

