<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2405211894 </F>
<F P=103> PA2405211894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic developments monitored through 24 May. 
  Planning and Economic Policy Minister Delia Cardenas has 
reported that the Inter-American Development Bank has formally 
notified the Panamanian Government that it has complied with all 
requirements for the first disbursement of a $180 million loan. 
The funds will be used to repair and build roads. A delegation 
from the Planning and Health Ministries is also in Washington 
negotiating a $25 million loan from the World Bank for the 
health sector. (Panama City LA PRENSA in Spanish 18 May 94 p 1) 
  In the first four months of the year, the Panama City 
Construction and Projects Department issued 940 permits for 99 
million balboas worth of projects, compared to 854 permits for 
64 million balboas worth of projects in 1993. This amounts to a 
more than 34 million balboa increase in construction 
investments. (Panama City EL SIGLO in Spanish 22 May 94 p 6) 

</TEXT>

