<H3> <TI>   New Justicialist Party Faction Launched </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Justicialist Party Faction Launched </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2505210394 Buenos Aires BUENOS AIRES HERALD in English 25 
May 94 p 11 </F>

<F P=103> PY2505210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires BUENOS AIRES HERALD </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A new branch of the Justicialist Party in the 
Federal Capital and Buenos Aires province was launched yesterday 
[24 May] by ultra-Menemists with deputy Erman Gonzalez and 
Restaurant Workers Union leader Luis Barrionuevo at the helm. 
The new faction, called Encuentro Peronista Bonaerense [Buenos 
Aires Peronist Movement], was the idea of some 30 Peronist 
political leaders and trade unionists. Barrionuevo told 
reporters in a press conference that the main platform for the 
new group would emphasize "getting back to Peronist basics such 
as health, education and unemployment." Later, Gonzalez said 
the group "will work in conjunction with the public and not via 
the media, which only seems to cater to other interests." 

</TEXT>

