<H3> <TI>   Court Upholds Former President Videla's Dismissal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Upholds Former President Videla's Dismissal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2505194094 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1401 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2505194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Buenos Aires, 24 May (NA) -- The Criminal Court 
has upheld the dismissal of former de facto President Jorge 
Rafael Videla in a case filed by the Interior Ministry for 
allegedly approving a crime. 
  Following Interior Minister Carlos Ruckauf's instructions, 
Alicia Pierini, the Interior Ministry under secretary for human 
rights, pressed charges following remarks he made during an 
amity dinner with retired military officers. 
  The former military officer noted that "he should have been 
given an award for his part in the struggle against subversion." 
Videla described himself as "a scapegoat of that struggle." 
[passage omitted] 
  The dismissal ruling mentions that Videla confirmed making 
the remarks mentioned in the charges, but, according to the 
judges, he did not maliciously seek to have his remarks 
published by newspapers or retold outside the group attending 
the dinner. 

</TEXT>

