<H3> <TI>   Numbers Game Documents Apparently Forged </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Numbers Game Documents Apparently Forged </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2605030394 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 24 
May 94 Section 1 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PY2605030394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Janio de Freitas] </F>
  [Text] The first technical test has not confirmed the 
authenticity of the typewritten sheets of paper that Rio de 
Janeiro Prosecutor General Antonio Carlos Biscaia presented as 
the numbers game kingpins' accounting sheets. 
  The test conducted by the Del Picchia Institute of Sao Paulo 
indicated that the sheets had not been prepared one month after 
the other, as monthly accounting sheets would have been expected 
to be. The test indicated that they had been prepared recently. 
  Biscaia did not allow an official test to be conducted. He 
used the documents as evidence in charges that involved bribery 
with money resulting from the illegal game, drug trafficking, 
and arms smuggling. Appellate Court Judge Gama Malcher ordered 
that the documents be tested again. 

</TEXT>

