BFN 

  [Text] Today, General Augusto Pinochet began his second 
trip abroad this year. He now has been invited by the Czech 
Republic. Army Deputy Commander Gen. Jorge Lucar and relatives 
saw Pinochet off at the airport. Pinochet did not speak to 
journalists. 
  The Army commander in chief is travelling with his wife and 
an entourage that includes Director of Logistics Brigadier Gen. 
Carlos Krumm Rojas and the Director of Army Ordnance Brig. Gen. 
Luis Iracabal Lobo. 
  It has been learned that during the 10-day trip, Pinochet 
also will visit Slovakia and Russia; he also may visit 
Switzerland and England. 

