<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Judicial Leaders Draft Note on Executive `Meddling' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Judicial Leaders Draft Note on Executive `Meddling' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2605013594 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2605013594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Darcey Quinn from the "24 Horas" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Judicial branch leaders expressed their solidarity 
with the Constitutional Court on 25 May. Prosecutor General 
Gustavo de Greiff, Supreme Court President Ricardo Calvete, 
State Council President Amado Gutierrez, and High Council of the 
Judiciary President Jose Alejandro Bonivento met for a luncheon 
that lasted more than five hours at the apartment of 
Constitutional Court President Jorge Arango Mejia. 
  [Begin recording] [Gutierrez, in progress] ...the court 
presidents and the nation's prosecutor general. We discussed a 
statement that will probably be issued on the afternoon of 26 
May. 
  [Reporter] Against President Gaviria? 
  [Gutierrez] No, no, no. A statement simply reaffirming 
constitutional principles. [end recording] 
  We learned, however, that the purpose of this inopportune 
meeting was to draft a communique in which the entire judicial 
branch protests the meddling of President Gaviria and the 
executive branch in the judicial branch's rulings. 
  [Begin recording] [Reporter] Do you think the government is 
meddling too much in judicial branch affairs? 
  [Gutierrez] No, I cannot tell you anything, because that is 
what the statement will deal with, and the statement will be 
issued on 26 May. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

