<H3> <TI>   Explosion Leaves Large Area of Quito Without Water </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosion Leaves Large Area of Quito Without Water </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2505201194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1925 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2505201194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Quito, 25 May (EFE) -- A large area of Quito was 
left without drinking water when two charges of dynamite 
exploded in the city's main water processing plant early 
yesterday. Today, the police continue defusing explosives in 
the installation, Patricio Ribadeneira, manager of the Municipal 
Drinking Water Enterprise (EMAP), stated. 
  The explosives destroyed the energy tower that allows the 
plant to function. No group has claimed responsibility for the 
attack, which "regrettably means the suspension of drinking 
water service in a large area of the city for several days," the 
manager noted. "The police are also helping workers of EMAP and 
the electricity enterprise handle the problem because some 
charges have not exploded and constitute an imminent danger, 
Ribadeneira added. 

</TEXT>

