<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Uruguayan Foreign Minister Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Uruguayan Foreign Minister Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2405205594 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 24 May 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> PY2405205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Uruguay's Foreign Minister Sergio Abreu Bonilla has 
said Uruguay does not support delaying the implementation of 
Mercosur [Common Market of the South]. He added that we must 
respect all legal instruments, such as the Asuncion Treaty, 
which established 1 January 1995 as the Mercosur launch date. 
  Abreu arrived in Asuncion this morning. He was received by 
his Paraguayan counterpart Luis Maria Ramirez Boettner. 
  Talking about his 3-day official visit, Abreu said he will 
discuss the common foreign tariff and other bilateral and 
regional issues with Paraguayan officials. He will also invite 
President Juan Carlos Wasmosy to the inauguration of the Martin 
Garcia Channel dredging, in Montevideo, on 10 June. Argentine 
President Carlos Menem is also scheduled to attend. 
  Tomorrow, Foreign Minister Abreu will sign various 
agreements 
and a joint declaration at the Foreign Ministry. 
  At 1600 this afternoon, the Uruguayan official will meet 
with 
President Wasmosy at the Government Palace. He will then 
continue his working meeting with Foreign Minister Ramirez 
Boettner. 
  On the morning of 25 May, Abreu will donate a computer to 
the 
Artigas School. At 1030, he will give a lecture at the 
Paraguayan Industrial Union (UIP) on the topic: "The Uruguay 
Round; The Results and Its Relation Within the Global Picture." 
Abreu will return to Uruguay at noon on 26 May. 

</TEXT>

