a coherent economic policy despite what other national sectors 
say. Batista argued that President Rafael Caldera has not broken 
his commitment of avoiding a sharp devaluation, but 
circumstances have prevented Caldera from complying with his 
goal. Finally, when asked about his dismissal, Batista 
indicated that the president is entitled to choose the 
