<H3> <TI>   Mass Transit Strike in Barinas; Disturbances Erupt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mass Transit Strike in Barinas; Disturbances Erupt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2505233094 Paris AFP in Spanish 2008 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2505233094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Barinas, Venezuela, 25 May (AFP) -- A mass transit 
strike today paralyzed the city of Barinas, 420 km southwest of 
Caracas, where student disturbances were reported even though 
the National Guard had occupied the city since early morning, 
according to the national news agency VENPRES. 
  Groups of students set several vehicles on fire and erected 
barricades at strategic points in the city to protest an 
unauthorized fare hike and a failure to apply reduced student 
bus fares. 
  Police spokesmen told AFP that as of noon, there were no 
reports of injuries. 

</TEXT>

