<H3> <TI>   Raul Castro Praises Work of Youth Labor Army </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Raul Castro Praises Work of Youth Labor Army </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2605173194 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0034 GMT 25 May 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2605173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 24 May (PL) -- Today, General Raul Castro, 
minister of the Revolutionary Armed Forces, praised the work 
done in the area of agriculture by the military youth 
detachments, and he said this is one of the corps of which he is 
most proud. 
  Castro, who is also second secretary of the Communist Party 
of Cuba, made this statement during a tour of three integrated 
farms administered by the Youth Labor Army (EJT) in Havana 
Province. 
  Raul Castro visited the the Kent Martyr labor unit in 
Artemisa Municipality, and the Calderon-El Cedro and La Flor de 
Cuba units in Alquizar Municipality, where he showed interest in 
crop yields, production costs, labor productivity, and rational 
use of fuel and other resources. 
  There, the pass system used by the young soldiers, their 
discipline, and the new organizational methods that have been 
introduced -- such as working in blocs (the concentration of 
manual labor and resources in one unit of land), which permits 
an increase in productivity and the saving of resources -- were 
all explained to him. 
  The Armed Forces minister congratulated the EJT members, as 
well as the civilian agricultural workers who assist them in 
their tasks, for the good results obtained, and he urged them to 
continue their efforts to overcome the difficulties caused by 
the lack of fertilizers and fuels. 

</TEXT>

