<H3> <TI>   Ministry Spokesman To Hold News Conferences </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Spokesman To Hold News Conferences </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2605213994 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0233 GMT 25 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2605213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 24 May (NOTIMEX) -- Today, Miguel Alfonso, 
official spokesman for the Cuban Foreign Ministry, said he will 
hold periodic meetings with the media to brief them on the 
Ministry's activities and to answer reporters' questions. The 
diplomat and scholar, who has been Ministry spokesman since 
April, said his appointment was due to a "need that had been 
felt for a long time." The Foreign Ministry spokesman is 
virtually the only official of his kind in the Cuban Government. 
  Alfonso said that during the meetings with reporters, he 
will 
brief them on the activities of Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina 
and other Ministry officials as well as comment on events in the 
area. He did not say, however, if officials in other ministries 
would assume a similar role. 
  The Foreign Ministry spokesman began his duties in April 
during "The Nation and the Emigrants" conference, which was 
attended by Cuban officials and approximately 200 exiles. On 
that occasion, Alfonso was introduced as a conference spokesman, 
but in ensuing weeks he continued as spokesman for the Foreign 
Ministry's routine activities. 
  The Ministry spokesman is a professor at the Higher 
Institute 
of International Relations and until last year was a member of 
the Cuban delegation to the UN Human Rights Commission based in 
Geneva, Switzerland. 

</TEXT>

