<H3> <TI>   PRD Joins Vote Count Review Under Protest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRD Joins Vote Count Review Under Protest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2705011994 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2338 GMT 26 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2705011994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Santo Domingo, 26 May (NOTIMEX) -- Today under 
protest, Representatives of the opposition Dominican 
Revolutionary Party (PRD), which nominated Jose Francisco Pena 
Gomez as its presidential candidate, joined the second day of a 
review of the Dominican elections. 
  After opposition parties filed charges of electoral fraud, 
107 electoral boards decided to review the vote count 
certificates for the 16 May elections, an activity which the 
[word indistinct] joined this Thursday under the premise that 
not all the certificates had been manipulated. 
  Pena Gomez said the fact that he is joining the certificate 
review does not mean he is validating the figures manipulated by 
the vote counting center. The politician said he will prove 
that the tens of thousands of people who supported him, which he 
described as a considerable number, are twice the number of 
those who supported the Reformist Social Christian Party (PRSC), 
which nominated President Joaquin Balaguer. 
  The PRD said the majority of its members could not vote 
because their names were not included on the voter lists even 
though they had their credentials. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

