<H3> <TI>   FRDH Asks Cedras To Respect Governors Island Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRDH Asks Cedras To Respect Governors Island Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2605191894 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2605191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Front for the Restoration of Democracy in Haiti 
[Front pour Restorer la Democratie en Haiti], FRDH, asks General 
Raoul Cedras to show goodwill by respecting the Governors Island 
agreement, which demands his early retirement and the return of 
constitutionally elected President Jean-Bertrand Aristide. 
  Since the enforcement of Resolution 917 of the UN Security 
Council, consisting of a total embargo, which has already been 
imposed on our country, we in the FRDH -- jointly with four 
other people's organizations -- cannot remain indifferent toward 
the suffering of the Haitian people. This is the reason we are 
again asking Gen. Cedras to show goodwill by standing behind his 
signature. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

