<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities monitored through 26 May. 
  The Economy Ministry has approved 9.5 million pesos in petty 
cash for the Presidential Secretariat, the Natural Resources 
Secretariat, the Drug Abuse Prevention Secretariat, the Science 
and Technology Secretariat, the Social Development Secretariat, 
and the Public Function Secretariat. (Buenos Aires CLARIN in 
Spanish 23 May 94 pp 16, 17) 
  On 19 May, business sources reported that Germany has 
implemented trade sanctions against Argentina for its delay in 
paying $7 billion in interest to the Paris Club. 
Argentine-German Chamber of Commerce sources indicated that the 
sanctions include the suspension of German loans, which are 
worth $300 million per year, to finance bilateral trade exports. 
The overdue interest involves loans contracted with German 
banks within the Paris Club to finance the Yacyreta 
hydroelectric dam project and the Atucha nuclear power plant 
project. (Madrid EFE in Spanish 1331 GMT 19 May 94) 

</TEXT>

