<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   PT Platform Includes Temporary Tax on Fortunes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PT Platform Includes Temporary Tax on Fortunes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2605191494 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 25 
May 94 Section 1 p 7 </F>

<F P=103> PY2605191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Francisco Santos] </F>
  [Text] If it wins the elections, the PT [Workers Party] 
will impose a temporary tax on large fortunes, in order to 
create a fund destined to finance projects for the creation of a 
large number of jobs. This information was supplied yesterday 
to FOLHA by economist Jose Marcio Camargo, one of the designers 
of the party economic policy. 
  The tax, which will be collected only in 1996, is one of the 
sources of money that the PT intends to use to create 8 million 
jobs during its government term. The party also intends to 
transfer 10 million workers from the informal to the formal 
sector of the economy. 
  According to Camargo, the fund to be created with the tax on 
fortunes will feed on the profits of the investments that were 
made. 
  Camargo added that another fund, which will be created in 
1996, will serve the same purpose, but no decision has yet been 
made on the source from which the money for it will be obtained. 
  Before creating this fund, the government will reportedly 
finance infrastructure projects for creating jobs with money 
from the budget and from social funds. 
  PT economists were due to meet last night in Rio de Janeiro, 
under federal PT Deputy for Sao Paulo Aloizio Mercadante, to 
debate the program for jobs creation and the party macroeconomic 
program. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

