<F P=100> Dominican Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fuel Smuggling Accidents Leave 19 Dead </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fuel Smuggling Accidents Leave 19 Dead </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2705183294 Paris AFP in Spanish 1659 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2705183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santo Domingo, 27 May (AFP) -- Armed Forces 
spokesmen report that 19 people have died and 42 others have 
been injured along the Dominican-Haitian border since the 
embargo on Haiti began to be intensified on Saturday. Citing 
military sources, local newspapers reported today that 
fatalities and injuries along the border have been caused by 
accidents involving vehicles that were smuggling fuel into Haiti 
and that were attempting to evade pusuing military vehicles. 
Over the weekend, the Dominican Army intensified its 
surveillance of more than 300 km of border with Haiti to prevent 
the smuggling of fuel into the neighboring country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

