<H3> <TI>   Deputy Claims Conditions To Overthrow Jonassaint Met </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Claims Conditions To Overthrow Jonassaint Met </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2705213194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2705213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Deputy Antoine Joseph, member of the Movement To 
Establish Democracy in Haiti and former lower chamber president, 
has asserted that the Jonassaint government is illegal and 
unconstitutional and that he does not recognize the current 
power's authority. Deputy Joseph believes the government that 
was installed by a group of legislators and not by the entire 
legislative corps operates beyond the constitutional provisions 
provided for in that respect. Deputy Joseph, who noted friction 
between the executive, the parliament, and the position of the 
political parties, considers that all the conditions have been 
met to overthrow the Jonassaint government. [passage omitted] 

