that France had been involved in this conflict for three years 
through giving weapons to some parties in the conflict and this 
added to the massacres among the ranks of the Rwandan people. 
The UN secretary general called for preparing a huge UN military 
force to send to Rwanda, which is witnessing a party and tribal 
conflict. 
  The JANA African affairs editor commented on this by saying: 
Western states are the ones that fabricate incidents and 
problems in many parts of the world with the aim of achieving a 
military intervention in those regions. 
  The editor wondered why international forces did not stop 
the 
racial and religious conflict in Bosnia and said that the 
dubious role of these forces in Somalia was known to all. 

