the hindrances imposed by the resolutions of the Security 
Council. 
  In his message he emphasized that the resolutions of the 
Security Council which imposed an air embargo on the Great 
Jamahiriyah were in essence purely political resolutions which 
had led to Libyan pilgrims being impeded in the performance of 
their religious duty securely, peacefully and easily and had led 
brotherly Islamic states to assist the Security Council in its 
resolutions by stopping the Libyan people from getting to the 
holy mosque in Mecca. 

