<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ministry Refutes 28 Apr Radio Statement </H4>

<F P=102> EA2904202994 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in English 
1600 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2904202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official source at the Defense Ministry, 
commenting on the so-called statement of the military official 
at the Ministry of Defense and the General Staff command which 
was transmitted by Channel One in Sanaa on 28 April said: 
  The Defense Ministry affirms that this statement was not 
issued by it and did not represent its opinion and that the 
statement was totally incorrect and had tried to change the 
facts upside down. It had tried in vain to place responsibility 
for the explosion of the situation in 'Imran on whom it referred 
to as saboteurs and secessionist elements in the Yemeni 
Socialist Party. The official source declined to answer this 
statement but the reality has already been made clear by the 
official source of the Defense Ministry last Wednesday [27 
April]. This fact is well-known by those who were burned by the 
fire of this sedition which was sparked off by the adventurous 
military command in Sanaa, the people of 'Imran and the members 
of the military commission who were present then at 'Imran Camp. 
  The statement added that the endeavors by the president and 
other officials in Sanaa to contain the position was totally not 
based on reality and that the appeals made by the defense 
minister to stop the military offensive against the 3d Armored 
Brigade had not been seriously dealt with. 
  The official source said that the ruling military circle in 
Sanaa had launched considerable forces equipped with various 
arms to attack the 3d Brigade without giving regard to the 
members of this brigade and the peaceful people of 'Imran. It 
also did not allow the evacuation of the wounded and did not 
treat them as prisoners of war but tortured them and 
interrogated them by the security bodies. 
  The source appealed to the public opinion, the military 
commission, and the fact-finding commission which was formed by 
the House of Deputies and human rights organizations to 
interfere in this inhuman conduct which contradicts with the 
morals of our Yemeni people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

