<H4>    Al-Bid, Mubarak Envoy Meet 29 Apr </H4>

<F P=102> JN2904201994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2904201994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman of the 
Presidential Council and secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party, tonight in Aden received brother Ambassador 
Badr Hammam, Egyptian assistant foreign minister and envoy of 
President Muhammad Husni Mubarak, who conveyed to him a message 
from his brother President Mubarak dealing with current 
developments, and the Egyptian leadership's concern about the 
escalation of these developments, and efforts to contain the 
crisis. 
  The meeting was attended by brothers Muhammad Salih Qutaysh, 
acting undersecretary at the foreign ministry--Aden branch, and 
'Ata Harun, the ambassador of the Arab Republic of Egypt in our 
country. 

