<H4>    Egyptian Envoy, Council Member View `Crisis' </H4>

<F P=102> JN3004173594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3004173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani, Presidential 
Council member, this afternoon received brother Ambassador Badr 
Hammam, the Egyptian assistant foreign minister, who is visiting 
our country. The ambassador reported on his talks in the 
economic and commercial capital Aden, within the framework of 
Egypt's brotherly efforts to contain the current crisis. His 
talks dealt with the latest developments in the crisis and how 
further complications can be averted. Brother 'Abd-al-Ghani 
told Hammam that Yemen appreciates brother President Mubarak's 
sincere efforts to contain and resolve the crisis, emphasizing 
that [words indistinct] with these efforts so that Yemen's 
unity, security, and safety are assured. The meeting was 
attended by 'Ata Harun, Egypt's ambassador to our country. 

</TEXT>

