<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Al-Bid Appeals for Help </H4>

<F P=102> EA0105151594 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1900 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0105151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Within the framework of contacts being made to 
contain the situation set off by influential [mutanaffidah] 
military forces in the General People's Congress on 27 April in 
the area of 'Imran, brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, deputy chairman 
of the Presidential Council and secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party [YSP] Central Committee, continued contacts with 
a number of his brother kings and presidents of Arab states. 
This evening he spoke on the telephone with the custodian of 
the two holy places, His Majesty King Fahd Bin 'Abd-al-'Aziz al 
Sa'ud, the king of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, His Excellency 
President Muhammad Husni Mubarak, the president of the Arab 
Republic of Egypt, and His Excellency Colonel Mu'ammar 
al-Qadhdhafi, the leader of the 1st of September Revolution. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid briefed the kings and presidents 
on 
the latest developments in the Yemeni arena, in light of the 
massing of troops and reinforcements by these forces, and the 
pursuit of soldiers of the 3d Armored Brigade in the mountains 
and areas close to 'Imran, as well as the treatment of the 
brigade's wounded as POW's in their own homeland. 
  He clarified that these forces are pushing the country into 
the inferno of a destructive civil war. He asked his brothers 
the kings and presidents to attempt to prevent this from 
happening, and to lessen the impact of the pschological and 
physical pressures from which the wounded are suffering. 

</TEXT>

