<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    YSP: Salih `War Speech' Caused Attack </H4>

<F P=102> NC3004204094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1920 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3004204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 30 Apr (MENA) -- A spokesman for the Political 
Bureau of the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] has accused the 
military forces in Sanaa of continuing their buildup to besiege 
and attack the 3d Armored Brigade in the new positions it 
assumed after the attack against it in 'Imran. 
  In a statement this evening, the spokesman said the 
aggression against the 3d Brigade in 'Imran was part of a 
military and political plan worked out by the General People's 
Congress [GPC] and the Yemeni Reform Grouping. The attack was 
launched after the "war speech" delivered by President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih on 27 April, he said. 
  The spokesman said President Salih is issuing instructions 
to 
chase and liquidate the 3d Armored Brigade and to send 
reinforcements from the Republican Guards and the Central 
Security forces. These forces, the spokesman added, are 
assisted by battalions from the al-Majd Brigade moved from Babil 
al-Jadidah [name as received]. 
  The spokesman said in his statement that the military forces 
in Yemen left the wounded from the 3d Brigade without medical 
treatment and sent them to jails. They are being treated as 
prisoners of war from a foreign army, not as the sons of the 
unified homeland. The spokesman urged Red Cross and Red 
Crescent societies and human rights organizations to extend the 
necessary assistance to those soldiers and to save them from 
torture. 
  The spokesman said the schemes currently being designed are 
part of a horrible bloody adventure that will deeply hurt 
Yemen's unity and security. 
  Attacking and chasing the 3d Brigade, the spokesman said, is 
a crime that will not pass easily because it means declaring an 
all- out civil war for which the separatists will be responsible. 
  Meanwhile, informed military sources in Aden have stressed 
that the military forces in Yemen continue to reinforce the 
Republican Guards, the Central Security, and the forces led by 
brothers and aides of President Salih in many governorates to 
escalate the military and political situation. 
  The sources said military reinforcements continued in the 
Governorate of Ta'izz toward al-Rahidah and Jabal Bani Shu'ayb, 
and the 3d Brigade was equipped to move toward the former border 
between the two parts of Yemen. 
  The sources added that the Republican Guards forces and the 
Central Security units in Dhamar were reinforced by two infantry 
battalions from al-Majd Brigade to besiege the southern Basuhayb 
brigade. President Salih and "his military family" are trying 
to push the biggest force possible toward the oil-rich 
Governorate of Shabwah, the sources added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

