<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Country's Political `Crisis' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    House Committee Continues Discussions </H4>

<F P=102> JN0105133194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 1 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0105133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tomorrow, Monday [2 May] the House of 
Representatives will resume its meetings under Brother Shaykh 
'Abdallah Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar, the House speaker. The people's 
deputies will discuss a host of issues on their agenda, as well 
as the latest developments in the country. 
  In a related development, the house committee made up of the 
Defense and Security Committee and other House members continued 
its meetings this morning. Conferees discussed the initial 
reports on the field missions carried out by the committee in 
the past three days. The committee visited the camps of the 1st 
and 3d Armored Brigades in the 'Imran area. The committee also 
met with the Joint Military Committee and listened to statements 
by shaykhs and citizens in the 'Imran area and by some officers 
and personnel on the circumstances of the regrettable events and 
their grave results. 
  The committee also reviewed the outcome of its visit to the 
military hospital to see the wounded personnel from the 1st and 
3d Armored Brigades. It reviewed the outcome of its visits to 
personnel from the 3d Brigade and the Signals Corps. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

