<H3> <TI>   `Source' Denies Development Minister's Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source' Denies Development Minister's Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2704153294 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1410 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2704153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 27 Apr (INA) -- An official Yemeni source has 
denied reports that Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, Yemeni minister 
of planning and development, has submitted his resignation. 
  In a statement to an INA correspondent, the official Yemeni 
source dismissed such reports as completely baseless. 
  In its latest issue, the opposition Yemeni paper AL-WAHDAWI 
said Dr. al-Irayni had resigned his ministerial post. The paper 
said the resignation was kept quiet to allow time to convince 
him to withdraw it. 

</TEXT>

